<p>
Let Us Help Wayanad is an initiative by the Kerala Government, launched in response to the tragic incidents of wayanad landslide. Driven by the principles of compassion, unity, and community support, this platform is dedicated to bringing immediate and targeted assistance to the people of Wayanad during times of crisis.
<br /><br />
To unite the efforts of caring individuals, organizations, and communities in providing essential support to Wayanad. Whether it’s responding to natural disasters, rebuilding homes, or supporting long-term rehabilitation, Let Us Help Wayanad serves as a bridge between those in need and those willing to help.
<br /><br />
At Let Us Help Wayanad, we focus on highlighting the specific needs of the affected communities—be it food, shelter, medical aid, or other essentials. By providing a transparent and reliable platform, we enable compassionate individuals to directly contribute to these needs, ensuring that support reaches those who require it the most, swiftly and efficiently.
<br /><br />
Let Us Help Wayanad operates under the guidance and ownership of the District Administration Wayanad and Information and Public Relations Department (IPRD), Kerala. Our platform is built on transparency, accountability, and community engagement. We work closely with local authorities, NGOs, and volunteers to ensure that every need displayed on our platform is verified and accurately represented.
